🚀 Just published: "Auxiliary-Loss-Free Load Balancing Strategy for Mixture-of-Experts" 🌐

Introducing Loss-Free Balancing—our latest innovation in MoE models that ditches the need for auxiliary loss. By dynamically adjusting expert biases, we ensure optimal load balance without the side effects of unwanted gradients. Validated on models up to 3B parameters, our approach delivers better validation loss and load balance than traditional methods.

Technical report: https://t.co/2hmDx0I4ah

To be specific, before the top-K routing decision, Loss-Free Balancing will first apply an expert-wise bias to the routing scores of each expert. By dynamically updating the bias of each expert according to its recent load, Loss-Free Balancing can consistently maintain a balanced distribution of expert load. In addition, since Loss-Free Balancing does not produce any interference gradients, it also elevates the upper bound of model performance gained from MoE training.

🎉Exciting news! DeepSeek API now launches context caching on disk, with no code changes required! This new feature automatically caches frequently referenced contexts on distributed storage, slashing API costs by up to 90%. For a 128K prompt with high reference, the first token latency is cut from 13s to just 500ms.  

Benefit Scenarios: 
- Multi-turn conversations where subsequent rounds hit the previous context cache. 
- Data analysis with recurring queries on the same documents/files. 
- Code analysis/debugging with repeated repository references.  

DeepSeek API disk caching is now live with unlimited concurrency. Billing is automatic based on actual cache hits. Learn more at https://t.co/Bjw7psHzyd

[4/5] Training Strategy
We argue that to ace the game, a Vision-Language Model really needs to nail the language part first 📚. To keep the language mojo from large language models (LLMs) rolling strong during pretraining, we're diving into a smart VL pretraining tactic 💡. Kicking off with a solid base in LLM training, we keep a keen eye on the tug-of-war between vision and language 🤼, steering them to play nice. Starting with a hefty dose of text, we then fine-tune the mix, aiming for that perfect harmony between the two 🎶.

[5/5] Performance
The DeepSeek-VL family 🌟, featuring both the 1.3B and 7B models, showcases superior user experiences in the real-world as a vision-language chatbot 🤖💬. They're rocking top-notch or super competitive scores 🏆 across a bunch of visual-language tests, all while staying the same size but still smashing those language-focused challenges 📚💪.

[3/5] Model Architecture
In light of real-life needs and efficiency, DeepSeek-VL rolls out with a versatile vision encoder. 🚀 This clever buddy can juggle high-res images (1024 x 1024) without breaking a sweat, all while keeping its token budget and computing workload on the chill side. 🧊 The magic? It ensures the model stays sharp, catching all those crucial bits and pieces across different visual challenges✨

Introducing DeepSeek Coder! 
- SOTA large coding models with params ranging from 1.3B to 33B.
- Building games, testing code, fixing bugs, and analyzing data... You dream it, we make it.
- Free for commercial use and fully open-source.
Try it out now at https://t.co/NlfpubcP9N https://t.co/gjP5WI4qIJ

Deepseek Coder achieves state-of-the-art performance among open-source code models on multiple programming languages and various benchmarks including HumanEval, MultiPL-E, MBPP, DS-1000, etc. https://t.co/XGYg5WpqyX

- Massive Training Data: Trained on 2T tokens, including 86 programming languages.
- Highly Flexible & Scalable: Offered in model sizes of 1B, 5.7B, 6.7B and 33B.
- Advanced Code Completion Capabilities: 16K window size, supporting project-level code completion and infilling. https://t.co/HcnWSzsPbo
